<div class="intro">

<h2>Scope</h2>
<p>
	SHARK is a modular C++ library for the design and
	optimization of adaptive systems. It provides methods for linear and
	nonlinear optimization, in particular evolutionary and gradient-based
	algorithms, kernel-based learning algorithms and neural networks, and
	various other machine learning techniques. SHARK serves as a toolbox to
	support real world applications as well as research in different
	domains of computational intelligence. The libraries are not
	necessarily dependent on any third party software. The sources are
	compatible with the following platforms: Windows, Solaris, MacOS X,
	and Linux.
</p>

<br>
